      "## How to Choose the Right POS System",
      "Before committing to a platform, evaluate your options against these criteria:\n\n**1. Industry fit.** A POS built for your retail category saves weeks of workarounds. If you sell phones, you need IMEI tracking.\n\n**2. Compliance readiness.** For Indian retailers, GST invoicing, e-invoicing (IRN), and HSN code support are non-negotiable.\n\n**3. Offline reliability.** Your POS should work during internet outages — critical for Tier-2 and Tier-3 locations.\n\n**4. Total cost of ownership.** Factor in transaction fees, hardware costs, and add-on charges beyond the subscription.\n\n**5. Scalability.** Check whether the platform supports multi-store operations.\n\n**6. Support quality.** When billing goes down during peak hours, response time matters.\n\nUse our [ROI calculator](/tools/roi-calculator) to estimate how much a purpose-built POS could save your store each month.",
